  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink277-kilavi">varaiyātu vantoḻukum talaimakaṉ puṇarntu nīṅkuḻi etirpaṭṭa tōḻi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> How the confidante, having encountered the hero—who kept coming without marrying—when he was about to leave after uniting with the heroine, urged him toward marriage.            
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink277">
<l>kuṟavar muṉṟiṉ mātīṇṭu tuṟukaṟ</l>
<l>kallā manti kaṭuvaṉō ṭukaḷuṅ</l>
<l>kuṉṟa nāṭaniṉ moḻiva leṉṟum</l>
<l>pacappa nītta leṉṉivaḷ</l>
<l>kayattuvaḷar kuvaḷaiyi ṉamartta kaṇṇē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from the land of the hill</l>
        <l>where the untaught female monkey,</l>
        <l>together with its male,</l>
        <l>leaps upon the thick stones</l>
        <l>touched by animals</l>
        <l>in the frontyard of the hill-dweller—</l>
        <l rend="space indent2">I [wish to] speak to you.</l>
        <l rend="space">Why do you always leave,</l>
        <l>so that [her] troubled eyes,</l>
        <l>like blue waterlilies</l>
        <l>that grow in the pond,</l>
        <l>become pale?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
